This letter from President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President Pro Tempore of the Senate provides a supplemental consolidated report on the deployment of U.S. Armed Forces equipped for combat. The report focuses on military operations in support of U.S. counterterrorism objectives, such as combat operations in Afghanistan against al-Qa'ida, the Taliban, and associated forces, as well as operations against the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL) in Iraq and Syria. The letter also mentions military operations in Somalia, Yemen, Djibouti, Libya, Jordan, Niger, Cameroon, and Egypt, as well as military operations related to the Lord's Resistance Army and the security of U.S. citizens and property in South Sudan. The President states that these deployments are carried out with the assistance of international partners and that the U.S. remains in an armed conflict against the Taliban. The letter concludes by affirming the President's authority as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive to direct these military operations.